					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7678857#post-4799186</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7678857/scp-4950#post-4799186</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 19 Oct 2020 00:52:03 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Riemann</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1787775</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Well, heck.</p> <p>Lines like</p> <blockquote> <p>Howard activates a shielding incantation from his cell phone and enters the summoning circle.</p> </blockquote> <p>and</p> <blockquote> <p>yeah but the archon lord needs millions of sacrifices. i have 213 minis</p> </blockquote> <p>are gold. They do a lot of heavy lifting for worldbuilding and characterisation.</p> <p>Unfortunately the rest of it is not really my cup of tea. It's a pretty straight &quot;what if X videogame was anomalous&quot; and the exploration log just felt contrived. I get the sense ARD felt the same way because they lampshade it at the very beginning.</p> <p>The idea that the lives don't need to be <em>real</em> lives is clever, but the article proceeds to not really do anything with it other than justify the incorporation of Fortnite. Which, ew.</p> <p>-1, but there are fantastic little snippets in this.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
