						 <p>You should really remove the spacing between the [[spans]] and the text elements in the phone call log. Right now, there's a line break after the span before the text on every span, which causes an awkward amount of space at the top of the text message bubbles.</p> <p>For reference, you have this:</p> <div class="code"> <pre> <code>[[span style=&quot;max-width: 300px; border-radius: 15px; padding: 4px 8px; display: inline-block; text-align: left; float:left; background-color: #739900; background: linear-gradient(to bottom right, #86b300, #5f8000); color: #fff;&quot;]] [[span style=&quot;text-shadow: #003 1px 1px;&quot;]] Hey I was doing some digging earlier today and I think I got something [[/span]][[/span]]</code> </pre></div> <p>When this looks much nicer:</p> <div class="code"> <pre> <code>[[span style=&quot;max-width: 300px; border-radius: 15px; padding: 4px 8px; display: inline-block; text-align: left; float:left; background-color: #739900; background: linear-gradient(to bottom right, #86b300, #5f8000); color: #fff;&quot;]] [[span style=&quot;text-shadow: #003 1px 1px;&quot;]]Hey I was doing some digging earlier today and I think I got something [[/span]][[/span]]</code> </pre></div> 
